# Enhanced Code Quality Standards

## Development Quality Gates
Before any code is written or modified, ensure:
- [ ] TypeScript compilation passes (`pnpm type-check`)
- [ ] ESLint rules are followed (`pnpm lint`)
- [ ] Code is properly formatted (`pnpm format`)
- [ ] All imports use absolute paths with `@/` prefix
- [ ] Components are wrapped in ErrorBoundary where appropriate

## Component Development Standards
- Use custom hooks for complex state logic (e.g., `useKlarna`, `useCheckout`)
- Implement proper error boundaries for components that might fail
- Use Zod schemas for all form validation
- Prefer composition over large monolithic components
- Always include proper TypeScript types - no `any` types allowed

## Error Handling Requirements
- All async operations must have proper error handling
- User-facing errors should be meaningful and actionable
- Console errors should include context for debugging
- Components should gracefully handle loading and error states
- Use ErrorBoundary for unexpected errors

## Security Standards
- Never expose sensitive data in client-side code
- Use proper environment variables for configuration
- Validate all user inputs with Zod schemas
- Implement CSP headers for XSS protection
- Sanitize dynamic content before rendering

## Performance Requirements
- Use React.memo for expensive components
- Implement proper loading states for better UX
- Use dynamic imports for code splitting when appropriate
- Optimize images and assets
- Monitor bundle size and performance metrics

## Testing Standards
- Write unit tests for utility functions
- Test error scenarios and edge cases
- Mock external dependencies (like Klarna SDK)
- Test accessibility features
- Validate form submissions and error states